## Dinarides region host 11 karst springs from 3 countries.

The Bosnian data is downloaded from the discharge annulas from the Federal Hydrometeorological Service of Bosnia and Herzegovina, and digitized by the data curator team.
The original data source can be accessed via "https://www.fhmzbih.gov.ba/latinica/HIDRO/godisnjaci.php".
The Bosnian data is open-access (equivalent to CC BY 4.0) without any restriction.

Slovenian data is provided by 
Natasa Ravbar (natasa.ravbar@zrc-sazu.si) and 
Cyril Mayaud (cyril.mayaud@zrc-sazu.si). 

Original data source of Slovenian karst springs is "https://vode.arso.gov.si"

Croatian data are accessed via 2 different platforms (i) WOKAS database, and (ii) the National Hydrometeorological Service of Croatia 
via the link "https://hidro.dhz.hr/".
The platform consisting of the surface flow measurements. We checked the stream gauging stations (with minimum upstream drainage) 
which are located at karst regions and assumed that these stations are representative for karst spring discharge. We also checked
the station photos (where provided by the dhz) and hydrograph shape to cross-validate the karst-specific rising and falling limbs.


The data cannot be downloaded as digital files, can be exported as visual formats (e.g. jpeg) for digitization, or downloadable in .html format.


For further information, please see Metadata table.
